00:47:02,650 --> 00:47:04,750
feel free to do so.

828
00:47:04,750 --> 00:47:05,750
Because,

829
00:47:06,380 --> 00:47:09,420
if this wasn’t bad enough there is
one more thing we need to talk about,

830
00:47:09,420 --> 00:47:12,900
that could make everything
a whole lot worse.

831
00:47:12,900 --> 00:47:17,944
The big thing that scientists worry about
are what they call tipping points.

832
00:47:19,339 --> 00:47:22,930
If the warming passes
certain thresholds,

833
00:47:22,930 --> 00:47:26,840
it sets off chain reactions
that speed up the warming even more.

834
00:47:28,055 --> 00:47:30,465
Each one of those tipping points
is like a booby trap

835
00:47:30,465 --> 00:47:33,539
that can’t be stopped,
once it’s set off.

836
00:47:34,709 --> 00:47:37,960
For example, by 2050,
the Amazon rainforest,

837
00:47:37,960 --> 00:47:40,610
because so much of it has been cut back,

838
00:47:40,610 --> 00:47:43,005
might reach the point
where the water cycle changes

839
00:47:43,005 --> 00:47:47,780
and the remaining forest dries out,
burns, and turns into a savannah.

840
00:47:48,751 --> 00:47:51,751
We’ll lose the most magnificent ecosystem
in the world

841
00:47:51,751 --> 00:47:56,612
and with it the indigenous communities
with their ancestral traditions and wisdom.

842
00:47:56,975 --> 00:48:01,700
And the smoke of half a continent will add
a whole new layer to the atmosphere.

843
00:48:02,330 --> 00:48:04,330
In Alaska, Russia and Canada,
the permafrost,

844
00:48:04,330 --> 00:48:08,410
the ground that is permanently frozen,
starts to thaw

845
00:48:08,590 --> 00:48:12,265
and it releases huge amounts of methane
into the atmosphere.

846
00:48:12,793 --> 00:48:16,728
A gas that traps eighty times more heat
than carbon dioxide.

847
00:48:17,730 --> 00:48:21,089
If we hit these tipping points,
things spiral out of control

848
00:48:21,089 --> 00:48:24,740
and we land in what scientists call
a “hothouse” scenario

849
00:48:24,740 --> 00:48:27,744
where climate systems shift
to something entirely new

850
00:48:27,744 --> 00:48:31,060
and civilization as we know it
is likely to collapse.

851
00:48:31,735 --> 00:48:33,374
These tipping points are
one of the reasons

852
00:48:33,374 --> 00:48:38,755
the United Nations and others say
we MUST keep warming below 2° Celsius,

853
00:48:38,755 --> 00:48:41,800
and preferably below 1.5°.

854
00:48:42,751 --> 00:48:44,510
Here is the crazy thing:

855
00:48:44,510 --> 00:48:47,290
if we don’t significantly change course,


856
00:48:47,290 --> 00:48:52,140
we might see a rise in temperature
of 2° Celsius by 2050.

857
00:48:52,140 --> 00:48:55,734
And that’s when some of the booby traps
might go off.

858
00:48:56,000 --> 00:48:58,240
